body:
Hello! I'm a huge fan of this tool and want to report a small bug I found with functions.

## Example of Bug

It appears that pairing argumentless functions with continuous assignment (`assign` or `wire` declarations) is broken. When running `vvp` on the output of the following example, I get the output `a.out:21: syntax error`.

```systemverilog
// test.sv

module test();

function automatic [7:0] test_func;
    test_func = 8'h1;
endfunction

// assignment by always_comb works
logic [7:0] test_alwayscomb;
always_comb test_alwayscomb = test_func();

// assignment by always_ff works
logic [7:0] test_alwaysff;
logic clk;
always_ff @(posedge clk) test_alwaysff <= test_func();

// assignment by assign broken
logic [7:0] test_assign;
assign test_assign = test_func();

// assignment by wire declaration broken
wire [7:0] test_wire = test_func();

endmodule
```

This is a summary of what `iverilog test.sv -g2012` generates
```plain
; a.out (summary)
v0x555555637a50_0 .net "assign_test", 7 0, L_0x555555637d00;  1 drivers
v0x555555637bd0_0 .net "wire_test", 7 0, L_0x555555637dc0;  1 drivers
L_0x555555637d00 .ufunc/vec4 TD_test.func_test, 8) S_0x5555556155d0;
L_0x555555637dc0 .ufunc/vec4 TD_test.func_test, 8) S_0x5555556155d0;
```
(Note the floating `)` in the `.ufunc` lines)


## Working Example

Note, this is what it would look like if the functions are passed an unused input. The code is read as expected.

```systemverilog
// test.sv

module test();

function automatic [7:0] test_func;
    input logic unused;
    test_func = 8'h1;
endfunction

wire [7:0] test_wire = test_func(0);

endmodule
```

```
; a.out (summary)
v0x555555dcfc20_0 .net/2s *"_ivl_0", 0 0, L_0x7f5acf055018;  1 drivers
v0x555555dcfd20_0 .net "test_wire", 7 0, L_0x555555dcfe00;  1 drivers
L_0x555555dcfe00 .ufunc/vec4 TD_test.test_func, 8, L_0x7f5acf055018 (v0x555555d8b290_0) S_0x555555dae950;
S_0x555555dae950 .scope autofunction.vec4.s8, "test_func" "test_func" 3 5, 3 5 0, S_0x555555d88c20;
v0x555555d8b290_0 .var "_unused", 0 0;
```

## Proposed Change

Support for this would require changing both iverilog, vvp, and the vvp spec.

### VVP Spec

[Structural Function Calls VVP Spec](https://github.com/steveicarus/iverilog/blob/b0c1eab51ed4eb32648ec20b6f07a3917ff07c67/Documentation/developer/guide/vvp/vvp.rst#structural-function-calls)

I propose that if there are no inputs, `<isymbols> ( <psymbols> )` should be omitted:

```plain
<label> .ufunc/real <flabel>, <wid>,
    [<isymbols> ( <psymbols> )] <ssymbol>;

<label> .ufunc/vec4 <flabel>, <wid>,
    [<isymbols> ( <psymbols> )] <ssymbol>;

<label> .ufunc/e <flabel>, <wid>, <trigger>,
    [<isymbols> ( <psymbols> )] <ssymbol>;
```

